HEADWORD: Synesis
<hw>Syn"e*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
intelligence.]</ety> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>A construction in which
adherence to some element in the sense causes a departure from strict
syntax, as in ⟦ldquo⟧Philip went down to Samaria and preached Christ
unto <xex>them</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Syngenesia</ent>⟦br⟧
